You can create an array with numbers from 0 to 10 in various programming languages. Here are a few examples:

### Python
```python
array = list(range(11))
print(array)
```

### JavaScript
```javascript
let array = Array.from({length: 11}, (_, i) => i);
console.log(array);
```

### Java
```java
import java.util.Arrays;

public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int[] array = new int[11];
        for (int i = 0; i < 11; i++) {
            array[i] = i;
        }
        System.out.println(Arrays.toString(array));
    }
}
```

### C++
```cpp
#include <iostream>
#include <vector>

int main() {
    std::vector<int> array;
    for (int i = 0; i <= 10; ++i) {
        array.push_back(i);
    }
    for (int num : array) {
        std::cout << num << " ";
    }
    return 0;
}
```

### Ruby
```ruby
array = (0..10).to_a
puts array.inspect
```

